parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic door release can trap passengers inside the vehicle, creating a significant safety risk in emergency situations.
symptoms: The interior door release button does not work
preventing passengers from exiting the vehicle
the button is loose in the door
and the door cannot be opened from the inside.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear camera can reduce visibility while reversing, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear camera screen flickers
goes blank
or displays an error message
making it difficult or impossible to see obstacles while reversing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of safety issues, including loss of critical systems, increased risk of accidents, and trapping passengers inside the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences electrical problems
including false vehicle theft alarms
"Pre Collision Assist Not Available" warnings
"Remote Features Disabled" notices
"Hill Assist Warning" detected a failure
rear camera flickering
Adaptive Cruise control not functioning
adaptive headlights not functioning
and Lane Keeping Assist warning and corrective non-functional.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument panel can cause a range of safety issues, including loss of critical information, increased risk of accidents, and trapping passengers inside the vehicle.
symptoms: The instrument panel displays incorrect information
including engine coolant levels
and can cause the vehicle to malfunction or shut down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of safety systems, such as the pre-collision assist system, can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The pre-collision assist system is not available
and the vehicle experiences other safety system failures
including adaptive cruise control and lane keeping assist.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: AdvancedTrac and Pre-Collision Assist System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the AdvancedTrac and Pre-Collision Assist systems can cause the vehicle to lose traction and stability, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Multiple warning messages appear on the dashboard
including "Drive Control Malfunction"
"Pre Collision Assist Not Available"
and "Service AdvanceTrac".

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Lane Keep Assist system can cause the vehicle to drift out of its lane, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to the left or right
and the system fails to keep the vehicle in the center of the lane.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the infotainment system can cause the loss of important features, such as navigation, voice activation, and Apple CarPlay, which can be a distraction and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The center screen goes black
and the system freezes or becomes unresponsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the backup camera can increase the risk of accidents or injuries when reversing.
symptoms: The backup camera image is lost
and the screen displays a black screen or a message to contact the dealership.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door switch can prevent easy exit during an emergency, increasing the risk of injury.
symptoms: The passenger door switch is inoperable
and the door cannot be opened from the inside.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the panoramic sunroof can cause injuries or accidents due to the sudden explosion of the glass.
symptoms: The panoramic sunroof explodes without warning
causing glass shards to enter the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended movement of the vehicle can increase the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle continues to move towards an intersection despite the brake pedal being pressed
or the vehicle moves by itself when shifted into drive or reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic stability control system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Multiple warnings on the dashboard
including Service AdvanceTrac
pre-collision assist not available
4WD fault service required
and Hill start assist not available; loss of traction; vehicle feels loose and difficult to steer; vehicle wants to swerve.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to hesitate, lurch, or lose power, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Unintended acceleration; vehicle hesitates or lurches forward; transmission fails to shift out of first gear; vehicle slips out of gear and RPMs increase without moving; burning smell through the vents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the all-wheel drive system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Warning light stating AWD malfunction; vehicle drives very loose and lacks firm control over steering; vehicle wants to swerve.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle moves while in reverse gear with foot on the brake; brakes are very stiff; vehicle stops abruptly
causing jerking motions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear view camera can reduce visibility while reversing, increasing the risk of accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The rear view camera displays a blue screen
black screen
or intermittent image; the camera image flips or is distorted; the screen displays guide lines only; the camera fails to display an image at all.
